Steps to reproduce:
1. Create short Ruby source file (say less than 10 lines of code)
2. Select some code at end of file.
3. Cut selected code
4. Immediately paste code back

The following exception is thrown
org.eclipse.jface.text.BadLocationException
	at org.eclipse.jface.text.AbstractDocument.getChar(AbstractDocument.java:732)
	at org.eclipse.core.internal.filebuffers.SynchronizableDocument.getChar(SynchronizableDocument.java:106)
	at org.eclipse.dltk.ui.text.util.AutoEditUtils.findEndOfWhiteSpace(AutoEditUtils.java:221)
	at org.eclipse.dltk.ruby.internal.ui.text.RubyAutoEditStrategy.handleSmartPaste(RubyAutoEditStrategy.java:253)
	at org.eclipse.dltk.ruby.internal.ui.text.RubyAutoEditStrategy.customizeDocumentCommand(RubyAutoEditStrategy.java:39)
......

A simple patch is (obviously the document is out of sync at this point, so
there is probably a better solution):

public static int findEndOfWhiteSpace(IDocument document, int offset, int end)
			throws BadLocationException {
while (offset < end) {
  //Start of patch
  if (offset >= document.getLength()) {
      return document.getLength();
   }
   //End of patch
   char c = document.getChar(offset);
.....
